Class SplitPackedArray

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.telenav.kivakit.core.collections.primitive.PrimitiveCollection
      • com.telenav.kivakit.core.collections.primitive.array.PrimitiveArray
        • com.telenav.kivakit.core.collections.primitive.array.PrimitiveSplitArray
          • com.telenav.kivakit.core.collections.primitive.array.packed.SplitPackedArray
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.esotericsoftware.kryo.KryoSerializable, PackedPrimitiveArray, LongIterable, LongList, PrimitiveList, LongCollection, Initializable, NamedObject, Countable, Sized, CompressibleCollection
    public final class SplitPackedArray
extends PrimitiveSplitArray
implements LongList, PackedPrimitiveArray
    SplitPackedArray maintains an array of packed arrays, indexing them as a single larger array. The purpose in this is to avoid resizing as a very large packed array grows. Instead, when a write index is greater than the size of the SplitPackedArray, a new PackedArray is allocated and added to the list. This design is similar to the "rope" pattern for handling very large strings.
    Author:
    jonathanl (shibo)
    See Also:
    LongList, PrimitiveSplitArray, SplitIntArray, SplitByteArray, SplitLongArray
